Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.14,1:48:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是8千萬 - 8千萬成交了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}No, eighty million! -Ok, so eighty million!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.36,1:48:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,8千萬，8千萬，這挺好的是吧\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Eighty million, eigthy million, that's good right?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.50,1:48:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,8千萬很好，謝謝你，非常感謝！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Eighty is great, eighty is great, thank you, thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.36,1:48:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,錢都匯到瑞士聯合銀行了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Most of them went to UBS
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.28,1:48:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你們運氣相當不錯\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You're very lucky!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.74,1:49:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,今天法國把國內最大的貨幣市場賬戶凍結了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}The largest bank in France froze it's customer's money-market accounts today
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.40,1:49:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,風暴已經傳到歐洲了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This thing is hitting Europe!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.04,1:49:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,希臘和愛爾蘭已經完了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Greece and Iceland are finished
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.00,1:49:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,西班牙正在遭殃\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Spain is teetering
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.34,1:49:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,真的假的？這麼嚴重\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Are you serious? Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.28,1:49:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,本，等你回家給我們打電話\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Ben call us when you get home!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.18,1:49:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,不過放電話之前請等一下\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}But hey, before you go... I'm just wondering...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.40,1:49:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直想問…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Uhm..
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.90,1:49:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你為什麼要和我們做這件事\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Why did you do this with us?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.16,1:49:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你並不需要…當然我們很感謝你…但\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You didn't have to, and eh.. you know, thank you, but, eh....
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.12,1:49:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,為什麼\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.68,1:49:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你們說想要發財，現在你們有錢了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You guys said you wanted to get rich! -Now you're rich!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.06,1:49:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,* 2008年3月14日\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}* 2008 March 14
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.14,1:49:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,房產和銀行還在持續出血 只有一家大單做空的還拒絕出售\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}As the housing-markets and banks continues to hemorrhage, only one of the big shorts refused to sell.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.96,1:49:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克·鮑姆的空頭（演講人 格林·斯潘）\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}*Keynote Speaker Alan Greenspan Mark Baum
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.84,1:49:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這簡直比咱們導演的還要好 他在會議上和布魯斯·米勒同台討論\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}So it was beyond perfect, when he was asked to speak at a conference opposite Bruce Miller
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.80,1:49:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,著名的樂觀投資人\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Famous bullish investor
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.68,1:49:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他和馬克辯論以後\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}After he and Mark had their debate
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.12,1:50:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,格林斯潘，整個金融危機的總設計師 還要繼續講話\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Alan Greenspan, one of the architects of the whole crisis, was scheduled to speak
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.72,1:50:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克辦公室的人都來了 把朋友也邀請過來了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Everyone in Mark's office showed up, even invited friends!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.74,1:50:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,這就像金融界的阿里和福爾曼的拳擊世紀對決\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This... was the Ali versus Foreman of the financial world
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.46,1:50:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,現實主義者對戰傻瓜\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Realists versus the fools
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.92,1:50:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們以為事情不可能更完美的時候 你敢相信…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And if it seems almost too perfect... trust me!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.46,1:50:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這事兒發生了！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This happened!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:16.54,1:50:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,歡迎大家的光臨\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Welcome everyone!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.72,1:50:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,* 貝爾股價 47\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}* Bear at 47
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.00,1:50:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,請讓我們熱烈歡迎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Please... Give a generous welcome to...
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.40,1:50:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,布魯斯·米勒和馬克·鮑姆\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mister Bruce Miller.... and Mark Baum
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.92,1:50:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,系好安全帶看戲了！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Strap yourself in!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.70,1:50:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你們有些人可能知道 貝爾斯登剛剛接受了一筆摩根的貸款\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}So as some of you may know, Bear-Stearns has just received a loan from J.P. Morgan
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.60,1:50:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,當然我們等些時間才能看到市場的反饋\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Of course we gonna have to wait to see how the markets react
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.52,1:50:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,但這事本身就能打消對貝爾銀行的擔心了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}But that should lay to rest any concerns about the bank self!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.36,1:51:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我理解，所以你本人不會出售你的2億股票了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}No, I take it, you have no plans to sell your two-hundred million in Bear stock
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.42,1:51:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,當然不，實際上等我們聊完 我還要再買進更多\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}No, as a matter of fact, when we're done here, I'll probably go buy some more!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.38,1:51:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,而對立觀點…馬克·鮑姆\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}For the opposing view... Mister Baum
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.34,1:51:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我得站起來說\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I gotta stand for this
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.20,1:51:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,好的，大家好\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Okay, Hi!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.06,1:51:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我們公司投資理念很簡單\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}My firm's thesis is pretty simple
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.90,1:51:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,華爾街把最初劉易斯房貸證券的好點子\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Wall-street took a good idea: Lewis Raneiri's mortgage-bonds
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.74,1:51:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了一個欺詐和愚蠢做成的原子彈\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And turned it into an atomic bomb of fraud and stupidity
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.38,1:51:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,現在原子彈馬上就要毀滅全球經濟了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}That's on it's way to decimating the world economy
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.10,1:51:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你說的還挺像那麼回事似的\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}How do you really feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.80,1:51:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我沒想到你現在還能笑的出來 我要是你的話可不這麼樂觀\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I'm glad you still have a sense of humor! I wouldn't if I were you!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.16,1:51:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,認識我的人都知道\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Now, Anyone who knows me, knows..
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.94,1:51:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我是對別人的錯誤直言不諱的\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}That I have no problem telling someone they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.68,1:51:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,（2008年3月14, 貝爾股票41點，39點）\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}*(2008 Mar 14) Bear at 41, Bear at 39
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.98,1:51:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你快看，股價還在往下泄\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It's a disaster, it just says here
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.22,1:51:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但這一輩子，我是頭一次… - 我的天\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}But for the first time.. in my life.. -Holy fuck!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.84,1:51:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,…真心笑不出來\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It's not so enjoyable
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.48,1:51:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,現在的美國充斥著欺詐\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}We live in an era of fraud in America
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.16,1:52:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,不僅是銀行，連政府也參與其中\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Not just in banking, but in government
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.06,1:52:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,教育，宗教\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Education, religion
Dialogue: 0,1:52:05.42,1:52:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,視頻，連棒球都作假\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Food, even baseball
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.36,1:52:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,真正讓我擔心的\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}What bothers me...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.22,1:52:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,並不是說欺詐不道德\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Isn't that .. fraud is not nice
Dialogue: 0,1:52:13.06,1:52:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,也不是說欺詐很邪惡\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Or that fraud... is mean
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.36,1:52:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,而是說，在過去一萬五千年的歷史中\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It's that .. for fifteen thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.28,1:52:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,欺詐和短視就從來沒有成功過\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Fraud and short-sighted thinking have never ever worked
Dialogue: 0,1:52:21.80,1:52:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,* 貝爾股價 37\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}* Bear at 37
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.64,1:52:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 一次都沒有 - 天哪\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Not once, eventually -Jesus
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.30,1:52:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 總會失敗 - 已經降到37了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You'll get caught -We're at thirty-seven
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.76,1:52:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- 行情要下跌了 - 這哪是下跌，這是暴跌\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Things go south! -It's fucking plummeting man, it's fucking plummeting!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.26,1:52:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我們難道都忘記教訓了嗎？\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}When the hell did we forget all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.74,1:52:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我還以為我們有希望，真的這麼以為過\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I thought we were better than this, I really did
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.46,1:52:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,還有\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And..
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.52,1:52:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然我們不夠明智 但是我也不覺得自己多麼正義，多麼驕傲\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}The fact that we're not, doesn't make me feel all-right and superior!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.52,1:52:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是為大家感到…深深的悲哀\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It makes me feel... Sad.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.28,1:52:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我每次刷新，股價都在掉 - 垮掉算了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Everytime i fucking hit refresh it's dropping man -And hope it does goes down!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.94,1:52:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,* 貝爾股價 35\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}*(Bear at 35)
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.46,1:52:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,看笑話的心情…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And as fun as it is to watch..
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.42,1:52:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,看這些自大愚蠢的華爾街人士大錯特錯\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Pompous dumb Wall-streeters be wildly wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.84,1:52:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,您也一樣，大錯特錯！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And you are wrong sir!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.08,1:53:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我只知道，最後…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I just know that at the end of the day
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.56,1:53:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,將是普通百姓來承受這些痛苦\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Average people are going to be the ones, that are going to have to pay for all of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.20,1:53:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 興亡總是百姓遭殃 - 32點\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Because they always, always do! -Thirty-two?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.52,1:53:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真是32點 - 這是跌破的節奏\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Shit! It's thirty-two -Yeah it's fucking tanked man
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.22,1:53:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我的拙見，謝謝大家\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}That's my two cents, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.34,1:53:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我得去德意志銀行去看熱鬧\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I'm gonna drop a deuce at Deutsche
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.92,1:53:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的樂觀派有什麼回應嗎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Does our bull have a response?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.98,1:53:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在華爾街的整個歷史上\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Only that in the entire history of Wall-street,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.74,1:53:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,從沒有投資銀行失敗，除非因為犯罪被牽連\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}No investment-bank has ever failed, unless caught in criminal activities.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.38,1:53:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我的回應是堅持！我認為貝爾前景光明\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}So, yes! I stand by my Bear-Stearns optimism.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.40,1:53:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,米勒先生，打擾了！一個小問題\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mister Miller, I'm sorry! quick question!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.96,1:53:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,剛才你們正在談話的時候 貝爾的股票已經跌落了38%\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}From the time you guys started talking, Bear-Stearns' stock is falling more than thirty-eight percent
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.00,1:53:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你還要再買入嗎？\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Would you still buy more?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.14,1:53:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Yeah, sure!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.50,1:53:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我當然要買入，為什麼不買\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Of course i'd buy more, why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.82,1:53:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,當場打臉\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Boom!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.20,1:53:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天哪 - 糟了 - 我們第一部分的討論就結束了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Jesus Christ! - Oh no! That concludes the first part of our presentation
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.90,1:54:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,下面我們有請，傳奇的前美聯儲主席 格林斯潘\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Up next, we have the legendary, former, chairman of the FED, Alan Greenspan!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.94,1:54:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,大夥\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Folks!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.08,1:54:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,* 貝爾斯登和國家銀行先後破產 * 現在輪到雷曼兄弟了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}* First Bear Stearns collapses, then Countrywide. * Now Lehman Brothers
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.28,1:54:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- …雷曼兄弟的員工… - 華爾街的大公司股票跌到零\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}... employees of Lehmann Brothers today, -as the Wall-street giant's stock went to zero!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.82,1:54:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,紐約銀行的形象毀於一旦\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}the collapse of the venerable New York Bank
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.18,1:54:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,之後將是幾個月的市場動盪 （2008年9月15日）\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Follows a tumultuous few months of market volatility * 2008 Sep 15
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.26,1:54:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們擔心世界經濟…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and fear for the world economy...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.88,1:54:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我得去裡面看看\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I gotta see inside
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.38,1:54:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼進去？\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}How?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.66,1:54:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,來吧\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Come on
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.34,1:54:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我電話忘到辦公室了，門卡也扔了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I left my phone in the office, I threw my pass out already,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:47.40,1:54:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- 能用你的嗎？ - 愛用就用，我才不管\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Do you mind if i take your pass? Borrow it? I don't give a shit anymore, you can do what you want!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.00,1:54:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,* 雷曼兄弟\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}* Lehman Brothers
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.14,1:55:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 直接上班車，別對媒體說話 - 18年了，我就落了這麼個結果\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Go directly to your transportation, do not talk to the press! -So that's it? After eighteen years!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:04.00,1:55:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,還趕我走，我願意怎麼幹就怎麼幹\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Go directly to your transportation, do not talk to the press! -I just leave? That's just fucking great, I can talk to whomever the hell I want!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.86,1:55:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,別對媒體說話\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Do not talk to the press!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.18,1:55:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,直接上班車，別對…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Go directly to your transportation, do not talk to the
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.98,1:55:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上想一起吃個飯嗎？\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Hey look, you want to get a bit tonight? There's this ehm...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.58,1:55:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,下東城那邊開了古巴餐館，可以去…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This new Cuban place just opened at the Lower East Side, so I suppose we could..
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.84,1:55:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是嗎 - 是啊\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Ah really? -Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.08,1:55:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,咱們倆\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You and I?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.66,1:55:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 也帶上大夥吧 - 好主意\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Yeah and eh.. other people -That sounds nice!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.54,1:55:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我很想去，謝謝你邀請我 - 總算打電話了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Yeah, I would like that, thank you very much! -Finally!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.00,1:55:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mark, Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.78,1:55:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,這裡已經血流成河了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It's a bloodbath up here
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.08,1:55:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,摩根股票貶值一半，跌到23，10\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Morgan's stock has lost half its value, it's down to 23,10
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.70,1:55:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,這是跌破的趨勢，我想和你談談脫身的事\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It's in a free-fall decline, so I wanted to talk to you about pulling their money
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.50,1:55:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,現在不把錢撤出來就沒機會了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I mean... It's now or never Mark!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.44,1:55:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我們要出手了！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}We gotta sell!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.94,1:55:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mark!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:52.82,1:55:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克，你聽到了嗎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mark, do you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.02,1:55:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,語音信箱1，您有15條留言\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mailbox #1, You have fifteen messages.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.92,1:56:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,麥克我聯繫不上你 你能方便的時候盡快回電話嗎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mike I can't seem to get a hold of you, could you please call me at your earliest convenience?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.44,1:56:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我是傑夫，你現在還要買股票？\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}It's Jeff, I.. eh.. You're buying stocks?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.16,1:56:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,現在是股市最低點，你太離譜了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}The market is at an all-time low, this is crazy!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.60,1:56:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我和我妻子是在網上認識的\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I met my wife on Match.com
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.40,1:56:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我的交友資料說我是個醫學院學生 只有一隻眼能用\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}My profile said that I'm a medical student with only one eye
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.40,1:56:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,不懂社交\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}An awkward social manner,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.34,1:56:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,助學貸款還有14.5萬要還\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and 145 thousand dollars in student loans
Dialogue: 0,1:56:24.60,1:56:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,她的回信是\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}She wrote back...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.24,1:56:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我找的就是你這樣的\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You're just what I've been looking for!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:28.82,1:56:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,她的意思是我很坦誠 那我也對你們開誠布公\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}She meant honest, so let me be honest...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.56,1:56:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,房地產危機是金融史上最大的機會\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}The housing-crisis represents the greatest financial opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.92,1:56:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但賺錢並不像我想象的那樣簡單\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Making money is not like i thought it would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.16,1:56:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,做交易…殺死了生命中對我最重要的那部分 這部分和做交易無關\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This business... Kills the part of life that is essential! The part, that has nothing to do with business
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.08,1:56:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,在過去兩年，我內心感覺到，黑暗的東西在自我吞噬\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}For the past two years, my insides have felt, like they're eating themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.86,1:56:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾經尊敬過的人\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}All the people I respected,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.48,1:57:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,現在再也不理我了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}won't talk to me anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.24,1:57:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,除了通過律師來找我\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Except through lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:06.94,1:57:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,人們…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}People...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.00,1:57:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,總希望有權威來告訴他們如何來選擇價值 但他們選擇權威\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Want an authority to tell them how to value things, but they chose this authority
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.68,1:57:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,並不是基於事實情況，或者成就\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}not based on facts or... results
Dialogue: 0,1:57:18.54,1:57:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他們這樣選，只是因為這些人看起來很權威 說出了他們想聽的話\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}They chose it because it seems authoritative...and familiar!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.48,1:57:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,可是…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.26,1:57:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我從未盲從過大眾\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I'm not, and never have been.... familiar
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.08,1:57:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,所以…\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}So..
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.10,1:57:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我得到了嚴肅的結論，我必須關閉基金\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}So I've come to the solemn realization that I must close down the fund
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.96,1:57:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,真誠的，麥克·貝利博士\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Sincerely, Michael J. Burry MD.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.54,1:58:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,* 盈利489% 賽恩淨值\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}*489% SCION VALUE
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.24,1:58:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,* 總盈利 26.9億\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}* TOTAL PROFIT  2.69 Billion
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.94,1:58:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,這和我想象的不一樣\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This isn't how I pictured it
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.92,1:58:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你以為是什麼樣的 - 反正不是這樣\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}What do you think you'd find? -I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.02,1:58:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,人人都做個成年人\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Grown-ups
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.42,1:58:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克，你聽著嗎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mark, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:59.80,1:59:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mark?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.92,1:59:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,財政部長和美聯儲主席剛剛離開白宮\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Paulson and Bernanke just left the White House.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.40,1:59:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,可能政府要出手了\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}There's going to be a bail-out
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.20,1:59:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不出手不行啊\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Well, they had to!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.54,1:59:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,是吧\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.08,1:59:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我們用擔保兌付房貸 - 這些人早就知道\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}We paid for mortgages with collaterals -They knew!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.56,1:59:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,ATM機回頭會取不出錢來的 他們必須阻止這種情況發生\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Cash would have stopped coming out the ATM, they had to back-stop this
Dialogue: 0,1:59:23.08,1:59:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,這些銀行家知道政府會用納稅人的錢保他們 他們不是愚蠢，他們只是不在乎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}They knew the tax-payers would bail them out, they weren't stupid, they just didn't care!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.04,1:59:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊，一幫騙子\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Yeah, 'cause they're fucking crooks!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.36,1:59:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但是走著瞧吧，肯定會有人進監獄的\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}But, at lest we're gonna see some of them go to jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.82,1:59:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是吧？\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.20,1:59:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,大銀行會被拆分\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}We need to gonna have to break up the banks
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.60,1:59:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不可能再為所欲為 - 我不知道，我不知道\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}The party is over! -I don't know, I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:46.92,1:59:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我總覺得，幾年之內 人們還是會和以前經濟危機一樣\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I have a feeling, that in a few years, people are gonna doing, what they always do when the economy tanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.98,1:59:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,責怪移民和窮人拖累了他們\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}They will be blaming immigrants and poor people.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.40,1:59:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,但是馬克錯了！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}But Mark was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:59.90,2:00:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,接下來的幾年，幾百個銀行和評級高管進了監獄\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}In the years that followed, hundreds of bankers and rating-agency's executives went to jail.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:04.58,2:00:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,證券交易委員會被政府徹查\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}The SEC was completely overhauled
Dialogue: 0,2:00:07.08,2:00:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,議會也迫於壓力不得不拆分大銀行\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and congress had no choice, but to break up the big banks
Dialogue: 0,2:00:09.90,2:00:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,進一步規範房貸和金融衍生品市場\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and regulate the mortgage and derivative industries
Dialogue: 0,2:00:17.32,2:00:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,上面開玩笑啦！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,2:00:19.00,2:00:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,銀行把人們投資的錢拿走\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Banks took the money the American people gave them
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.34,2:00:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,用來給他們自己開巨額獎金\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and used it to pay themselves huge bonuses
Dialogue: 0,2:00:23.62,2:00:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,然後賄賂議會，來駁回激進的改革\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and lobby the congress to kill big reform
Dialogue: 0,2:00:26.14,2:00:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,然後再把鍋甩到移民和窮鬼身上\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and then they blamed immigrants and poor people
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.58,2:00:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,這次，連教師也跟著被指責\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}and this time even teachers!
Dialogue: 0,2:00:31.84,2:00:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,這些都說完做完以後，只有一個銀行家被關了監獄\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}And when all was said and done, only one single banker went to jail
Dialogue: 0,2:00:35.78,2:00:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,這個倒霉蛋！\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}This poor schmuck!
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.98,2:00:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,瑞士瑞信銀行的卡里姆\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Kareem Serageldin from Credit Suisse
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.92,2:00:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他在房貸證券中損失了幾十億\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}He hit a few billion in mortgage-bond losses
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.18,2:00:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但對金融危機的大銀行來說 這些損失都是平常事兒\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Something most of the big banks did on a good day during the crisis
Dialogue: 0,2:00:47.20,2:00:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,馬克，我們能出手了嗎\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}Mark, can we sell now?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:50.48,2:00:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,現在基金能回收10億\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}I mean the fund will almost make a billion dollars
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.60,2:00:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你能清算出2億來\N{\b1\fs12\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&}You'll clear two-hundred mill Mark!
